cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you reference this protocol, its design document, or its criteria, please cite it as below."
title: "No Shit"
type: software
repository-code: "https://github.com/ConSenseAI/no-shit"
authors:
  - family-names: Helvick
    given-names: Scott
  - name: Consense
license:
  - CC-BY-4.0
  - Apache-2.0
keywords:
  - enshittification
  - attestation
  - dark patterns
  - anti-extraction
  - software certification
  - LLM audit
  - agent-mediated commerce
abstract: >-
  A public-good protocol for machine-verifiable, criterion-specific claims
  about the anti-extraction properties of software: multi-model LLM consensus
  audits run in trusted execution environments against public, versioned
  criteria, publishing signed attestations that buyers' agents, procurement
  teams, and assistant-class AI can verify and filter on.
